- "rental activity" refers to the total number of rentals made by a customer;
- "review counts" refers to the total number of reviews submitted by a customer;
- "staff efficiency" includes the number of rentals processed by a staff member and the average rental duration they handle.

- An "active promotion" is a promotion where `is_active` is set to 1, indicating it is currently running.;
- A "latest approved review" is a customer review that has been approved by a staff member and is the most recent one for that film.;
- "Promotion end date" refers to the date when the promotion will no longer be active.;

- "The king of the cinema" refers to the customer who has rented the most films;
- "The prince in the realm of movie enthusiasts" refers to the next customer in terms of the number of films rented;
- "Film lover" and "movie enthusiast" are metaphors for customers who frequently rent films;
- "Membership status" indicates whether the customer is a regular or premium member;
- "Average film rating" is the average rating given by the customer to the films they have reviewed.

- "active promotions" refer to promotions where `is_active` is set to 1;
- "rental duration" is calculated as the difference between the `return_date` and `rental_date` in days;
- "preferred genre" is the genre that a customer has rented the most.

- 'Blossomed into the light after the dawn of the new millennium' refers to films released after 2000;
- 'Gentle 'G' rating' refers to films with a 'G' rating;
- 'Guardians of the store's inner sanctum' refers to staff members with the 'admin' role;
- 'Generous average discount rate of more than 10%' refers to an average discount rate greater than 0.1;
- 'Seen more than 10 rentals' refers to a count of rental transactions greater than 10.

- 'Shining stars' refers to the films with the highest rental counts;
- 'Drawing the most viewers to the rental shore' means the films that have been rented the most;
- 'Alphabetical parade' refers to the alphabetical order of film titles;
- 'In the case of a tie' means when multiple films have the same highest rental count within a genre.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(film_id) 
FROM films 
WHERE genre_id = 1 AND rental_rate > (SELECT AVG(rental_rate) FROM films);

external_knowledge:
- Active promotions are those where `is_active` is set to 1;
- A film is considered "currently rented" if its `rental_status` is 'active';
- The rental revenue is adjusted by the discount rate if a promotion is active;
- The average rental revenue is calculated by dividing the total revenue by the total number of rentals.
